gujarati.context:
Here are the translations:

They joined hands with this promise, then didn't keep their word; 
Now know for yourself that there is a third one, you shouldn't keep it in your heart.

Here is the translation:

The land has a Brahmin's name, Lord of Ishwar there; 
If he gets angry, grief will not come to him, calm will be.

After death, the ghost studied and begged to go; 
The virtuous Ishwarji became available; 
That great king Pratap Shrimaharaj was like that; 
What would be spoken from mouth again and again?
